related_questions.question: What activities can you participate in at UC Davis?
related_questions.snippet: Active Campus Recreation members may take as many group exercise, dance, martial arts, and small group training classes as they'd like each quarter with a GX Pass! It's just $35 per quarter or $75 for the academic year.
related_questions.title: Home | Campus Recreation - UC Davis

related_questions.question: Does UC Davis have a recreation center?
related_questions.snippet: UC Davis Campus Recreation is an inclusive environment where everyone is welcome regardless of background or level of experience. With six centers, 11 program areas and five outdoor fields, Campus Recreation can help you find your center.
related_questions.title: Programs and Facilities - UC Davis Campus Recreation

related_questions.question: Does UC Davis have a free gym?
related_questions.snippet: Campus Recreation memberships are based on the university's academic calendar; access is therefore granted based on student fees. In other words, your Campus Recreation membership is only active during quarters or semesters in which you are enrolled in classes and paying fees.
related_questions.title: Membership Pricing - UC Davis Campus Recreation

related_questions.question: What is in a recreation center?
related_questions.snippet: Promoting community fitness Your average community center might offer facilities like gyms, pools, and sports courts where people can work out how they want. They'll often host specialized training programs like yoga, Zumba, and pool fitness, or wellness training events like nutrition workshops.
